
1. External Style Sheets:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Inclusion Application</title>
       <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="main.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <h2>The CSS Application Tutorial</h2>
        <p>Welcome to Software Developer tube channel!</p>
        <p>We look at the how CSS is used to style webpage.</p>
        <p>Welcome to Software Developer tube channel!</p>
        <p>We look at the how CSS is used to style webpage.</p>
    </body>
</html>

main.css

h2 {
    color:#ff00ff;
    border: 5px solid #000000;
    text-align: center; }
p { color: #ff0000;
    background-color: #c0c0c0;
    padding: inherit;
}

2. Embedded Style Sheets:

    <head>
        <title>CSS Inclusion Application</title>
        <style>
h2 {
    color:#ff00ff;
    border: 5px solid #000000;
    text-align: center; }
p { color: #ff0000;
    background-color: #c0c0c0;
    padding: inherit;
}
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h2>The CSS Application Tutorial</h2>
        <p>Welcome to Software Developer tube channel!</p>
        <p>We look at the how CSS is used to style webpage.</p>
        <p>Welcome to Software Developer tube channel!</p>
        <p>We look at the how CSS is used to style webpage.</p>
    </body>

3. In-line Styles Sheets:

    <head>
        <title>CSS Inclusion Application</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h2 style="color:#ff00ff; border: 5px solid #000000; text-align: center;">The CSS Application Tutorial</h2>
        <p style="color: #ff0000; background-color: #c0c0c0; padding: inherit;">Welcome to Software Developer tube channel!</p>
        <p style="color: #ff0000; background-color: #c0c0c0; padding: inherit;">We look at the how CSS is used to style webpage.</p>
        <p style="color: #ff0000; background-color: #c0c0c0; padding: inherit;">Welcome to Software Developer tube channel!</p>
        <p style="color: #ff0000; background-color: #c0c0c0; padding: inherit;">We look at the how CSS is used to style webpage.</p>
    </body>
